# Auth Federation

- Vendor identity must come from authenticated identity context, not request body fields.
- Use `IDP_VENDOR_CLAIM` as the vendor claim source (default `bcpAuth` in policy decisions unless overridden by environment).
- Policy checks must block source-vendor spoof attempts when body/source input disagrees with authenticated vendor.
- Keep admin endpoint enforcement centralized through policy helpers and JWT (admin role) validation; no x-admin-secret.
